          <td bgcolor="#BF003F" valign="top"><!-- #BeginEditable "Body" --> 
            <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
<tr><td align="left" valign="bottom" width="98%"><img src="/starwarsccg/gfx/theme1/toptab.gif" width="98" height="10" border="0" vspace="0" hspace="0"></td><td align="left" valign="bottom" width="22">&nbsp;</td></tr>
<tr><td bgcolor="#3F403F" width="98%" class="cheader"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Tournament Reports</td><form method='post' action=''><input type="hidden" name="PHPSESSID" value="...328fedb22570524062aeb1303" /><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Tournament Reports</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/starwarsccg/treports/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/heroclix/treports/treports.php'>HeroClix</option><option value='/vs/treports/treports.php'>Marvel VS</option><option value='/lotr/treports/treports.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/treports/treports.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/treports/treports.php'>Ophidian 2350</option><option value='/magic/treports/treports.php'>The Wastelands</option></select></td></form></tr></table></td><td bgcolor="3F403F" valign="top" align="right" width="22"><img src="/starwarsccg/gfx/theme1/topcorner.gif" width="23" height="22" border="0" vspace="0" hspace="0" align="right"></td></tr>
<tr><td width="98%" colspan=2><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="5" class="cbody">
<tr><td><font class="h1font"> Kalamazoo, MI March 12, 2005<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/starwarsccg/gfx/theme1/star.gif" width="19" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/starwarsccg/gfx/theme1/star.gif" width="19" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/starwarsccg/gfx/theme1/star.gif" width="19" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/starwarsccg/gfx/theme1/star.gif" width="19" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/starwarsccg/gfx/theme1/star.gif" width="19" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(5.00)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/starwarsccg/main/mpage.php?member=14472'>Brandon "Mr. blp" Pahl</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/starwarsccg/main/mpage.php?member=14472&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> March 31, 2005</font><p align='justify'><blockquote><font class="bfont"> It has been almost two weeks since the tournament and I may not have remembered every single detail so I am apologizing ahead of time if any of the facts that I present are different from what other people remember. Also, this thing is damn long and I am lazy so after writing it, I didnt bother going through it to check the grammar, spelling and punctuation. But feel free to do so if you want to!<br />
<br />
At about 5:30 am the alarm breaks through my peaceful slumber, rudely waking me up and forcing me to confront the cold reality that is my wifes hardwood floor. Not pleasant. So after dragging my sorry butt into the shower then waking up Adam, we head out to Tim Hortons to meet Spencer and Andy. They dont show up until 7:30ish which gives me and Adam plenty of time to properly caffeinate ourselves to the point of giddiness. Finally after parking Andys car we all pile into my piece of junk and start out on a 4 hour 21 minute driver to Kalamzoo, Michigan from London, Ontario in Canada, for the sole purpose of playing a collectible card game. Yeah my wife thought we were crazy too.<br />
<br />
Of course I forget to get gas in town and it is not until we are cruising on the 401 West in the middle of nowhere does Spencer point out that we are in fact doing our cruising on an empty tank. Now, when I say the middle of nowhere, I mean that on one side of us is trees and fields and on the other side of us istrees and fields and the last sign we passed said Next Town 62 km. At this point Im kinda glad that I have CAA and a cellphone. But wait! Whats this! It would seem that Spencer has a third Grandma from a second marriage involving a twice removed Uncle or something to that extent who used to, or still does, live in the area (its been two weeks now so my facts may be a little hazy). At any rate, Spencer tells me to get off at the next exit and go north. So we end up in some quant town called Forrest or something Robinhoodish. Either way, we fill up and set our course for Kalamazoo. <br />
<br />
We arrive at the border at about 9:20ish and proceed to meet one of the laziest border security agents I have ever met. This guy didnt even bother looking at our id or anything. He just asks us, Where are you going? I answer Kalamazoo for a convention. What kind of convention? A Star Wars convention. You know, nerd stuff. With that, he smirks and lets us go. Maybe he felt that a carload of nerds were not worth investigating. Hell, we coulda been 4 pot smoking gay guys on our honeymoons, heading to the States in an attempt to subvert the morals and ethics of Americans everywhere with our left wing free thinking Canadian propaganda! Lucky for that guy though we were just there to play cards. At this point we start out on the I-69. As for the rest of the drive:<br />
<br />
9:38 - By now we are feeling a bit hungry and Adam  <br />
       recommends that we try the <br />
       breakfast burritos at McDonalds. According to him <br />
       they are quite tasty. With much hesitation,we <br />
       pull over at the nearest McDs and decide to go in <br />
       for the food to stretch our legs. To our surprise <br />
       we are told that only the drive through is open at <br />
       this hour, so we are forced to sit in our car and <br />
       further pollute the environment as we wait for our <br />
       food.<br />
<br />
9:45  We pass an accident involving two cars in the <br />
       middle of the road. The breakfast <br />
       burritos turn out to be a lot better then anything <br />
       from Mcds deserves to be.<br />
<br />
10:26  We pass another accident on the side of the road. <br />
        We notice at this point that <br />
        there are a large number of pylons scattered <br />
        everywhere on the side. Probably because it would <br />
        seem that every road we pass seems to be under <br />
        construction. <br />
<br />
11:00  We pass a car that is just sitting on the side of <br />
        the road. The breakfast burritos from McDs do not <br />
        seem to be such a good idea anymore. More pylons.<br />
<br />
11:10 - At this point the highway we are on just <br />
        inexplicably ends in a huge row of <br />
        pylons and  we are forced on to some side road <br />
        that leads to some place where we dont want to <br />
        go. Our tour of the state of Michigan begins.<br />
<br />
11:20  We pass a car in a ditch. I almost hit a pylon. At <br />
        this point I am getting a little <br />
        worried about where we are and where we are going. <br />
        also notice that there are gas stations everywhere <br />
        called BP everywhere. I find this amusing since my <br />
        initials are BLP! LOLOLolololloloollsigh..<br />
<br />
11:36  We pass yet another accident on the road. It looks <br />
        like they hit some of those pylons. By this time <br />
        we have no idea where we are in Michigan. <br />
<br />
12:00  By this point we have now circumnavigated our way <br />
        through most of Michigan and somehow ended up on <br />
        the I-94. Map Quest has utterly failed us as we <br />
        continue to hurtle towards the unknown. We also <br />
        pass a car in the ditch with its windows blown <br />
        out. I am starting to be concerned about the <br />
        driving abilities of people who live in Michigan. <br />
        More Pylons.<br />
<br />
12:15  We stop for gas and directions. A guy at the BP <br />
        gas station tells us that Kalamazoo is another <br />
        hour and a half away and thats going 70 miles per <br />
        hour the whole way. Realizing that the tournament <br />
        starts in less than an hour, I get back in the car <br />
        and start doing 90 miles per hour, or about 145 <br />
        kilometers an hour for everyone else who is metric.<br />
<br />
12:46  We pass another car in the ditch, but this one is <br />
        backwards, which stumped me for a while until I <br />
        realize that he probably spun out of control and <br />
        ended up backwards in the ditch trying to avoid a <br />
        pylon.<br />
<br />
We finally arrive in Kalamazoo right before 1:00 pm, breathing a sigh of relief. Unfortunately though, Kalamazoo has one of the most ridiculous street layouts that I have ever experienced, and it takes us forever to find the place. In fact, the place is on the Michigan University campus. No problem. I say, We can just park and find the properly numbered building. Little do we know though, is that the WHOLE campus is 1903 Michigan Av. W, which is the address of the tournament. So we get out and start wandering around looking for any people who may be here for a nerd convention. At one point, Andy and Spencer wander into a building and we lose them. So me and Adam end up wandering around the campus, hoping that fate will somehow intervene and guide us to the tournamentor barring that, we would meet some hot university chicks. Lucky for us though, I overhear a guy standing outside a building talking with two other guys about how his level 13th thief can kick the crap outa his friends level 9th ultra paladin and how his vorpal sword of geek slaying +18 makes him undefeatable or some such crap.so I figure we are on the right track. We head inside the building to find a really big room filled with hundreds of ill adjusted people similar to the three standing out front. We meet up with Andy and Spencer, turn in our deck lists and get ready for game 1.<br />
<br />
My weapons of choice for the day were My Kind of Scum with Greedo as my rep and the Big Disco Party, otherwise known as Profit. I had been playing both decks for a while and felt very comfortable with them. I wont go into details concerning my two decks here (god knows this is already long enough), but if you want to see them, check em out on Decktech. The light side deck is called Big Disco Party and the dark side is Gardulla Goes to the Disco.&quot; <br />
<br />
Game 1: Kevin the CubsFans MBO vs. my Scum<br />
This is what is so great about traveling around and playing in all these tournaments. I get to meet the people behind the decks and nicknames I see on Decktech and the PC site. <br />
I start Twilek V and grab Power of the Hutt, Jabbas Influence V, Ket Maliss V and Hutt Bounty V, Tatooine: Desert Heart and Tatooine: Jabbas Palace. He starts Squassin and some other stuff that I cant remember. <br />
<br />
On my first turn I drop Jabbas Barge with Power of the Hutt, the lower deck, a rodian, URRURrururURRuruRuRuURruURuRuR, his Bantha all at the desert heart, a JP site from reserve and pull Greedo into my hand with Ket Maliss. <br />
<br />
On his first turn he drops three guys onto Yavin 4 along with a bunch of sites, flipping his objective, pulls out the Battle Order shield, consolidates his forces on Yavin and draws into his hand. I pay to drain for 3 at the desert, and proceed to drop Jabba V, Reflections 3 Bib, Lando and some other junk on Tatooine, along with Scum and Villainy. I also drop JQuille V on Yavin 4, causing him to lose 3 or 4 force and use my last force to move him away, letting him chill at the Massassi Headquarters. <br />
<br />
On his second turn, he drops down a Rebel Tech V, some systems, the Death Star, the trench, LT. Blount, Tala 2 and Luke aboard R5 with some torpedoes. He goes in to blow up the happy funball of death while I cringe at the prospect of losing 14 force on only my third turn. Lucky for me he draws Kiffex and a 1 for his destiny. He then moves over his guys on Yavin to block my JQuille drain. <br />
<br />
My third turn, I am holding ZiMH and BiHT in my hand while he has Luke and Blount loitering at the Death Star. I figure that its do or die at this point so I drop them both at the Death Star and go in for the kill. For destiny I draw a 4 and a 5. Because of ZiMH he gets a big fat zero for destiny, allowing me to keep both my ships there. He loses Luke and Blount and I breathe a big sigh of relief. <br />
<br />
On his third turn, he deploys Entrenchment and initiates battle against the all powerful JQuille , causing me to lose 2 force from overflow. After he draws into his hand it is my fourth turn. I drain a whole bunch on the ground while he cancels one of them with Entrenchment. I go digging for Jabbas Cruiser via Power of the Hutt and drop it with Xizor to Tatooine. While I am in there I go looking for Bane Malar V and use Bibs game text (read it, it rocks) to place my force pile on my used pile to activate the rest of my reserve deck, allowing me to draw him onto my hand.<br />
<br />
At this point in the game, I am draining for on average 7-8 force a turn for free, while he draws into his hand in hopes of setting up a second attack run. Somewhere around the 6th turn he drops Luke back down and successfully blows up the happy funball of death, causing me to finally lose my 14 force. By then though it was too late for him. He managed to retrieve a couple force from deploying some ships and got in a few drains that I simply canceled with Greedo on my objective but he could not compete with the steady force loss I was causing through my drains.<br />
<br />
FW +13<br />
<br />
Highs:<br />
Beating Kevins MBO. I felt kinda bad since he was such a nice guy about it.<br />
<br />
Lows:<br />
The look on Kevins face when he drew the zero and 1 for his first attempt at blowing up the Death Star.<br />
<br />
<br />
Game 2: My Profit vs. Andys new age Hoth Walker deck.<br />
So I drove 5 hours to play the same guy who I almost always play at every tournament in Toronto. I would say that I am the favourite going into this match up. Andy hasnt beaten me in a while, although as soon as I see the Hoth stuff, I have a bad feeling in the pit of my stomach. He starts Combat Readiness V which gets him, Hoth, the Ice Plains, the Docking Bay, You May Start Your Landing, Prepare for a Surface Attack and Combat Response. I start Civil Disorder V, Seeking an Audience V and Colo Claw Fish. <br />
<br />
His first turn, he goes and grabs the 3rd marker and a Walker Garrison. He drops Blizzard 4 and grabs Captain Bewil V to the 3rd marker and draws the last couple of cards up into his hand. On my turn, I deploy the Coruscant Jedi Chamber, Naked Threepio to Tatooine, drop a six on the fish and go in like a mad man against Blizzard 4 with EPP Luke. I clear the site but lose Luke in the process. <br />
<br />
The next turn he drops an Ice Storm to the Ice Plains and No Escape, making the Honor of the Jedi I just drew into my hand useless. He deploys Woof and Jabbas Cruiser to the Hoth system and a walker to the 5th marker. On my turn, I do the Threepio thing and end up drawing into my hand in the hopes that I will get something I can use. <br />
<br />
His third turn, he drains at the system and I lose one force from You May Start Your Landing. He moves the Ice Storm to the 3rd marker, deploys a few more guys to space and some foil Japanese Hoth 2 player set walkers to the 3rd marker and docking bay, letting him deploy Rebel Base Occupation. He moves all his walkers over to the 3rd marker, pulls the Firepower shield and lets me go. At this point I have an epiphany; Holy Crap!! I realize that he is about to start stomping all over me and I have barely touched him. Not wanting to walk into his Ice Storm, I drop the Naboo: Battle plains with EPP Obi-wan along with Chewbacca Protector V in the hopes that I can get some drains in. <br />
<br />
I lose 5 force on his next turn and he gets to retrieve a card with Firepower because I didnt battle him. He continues to throw down walkers onto Hoth and more guys in space and moves the Ice Storm back onto the Ice Plains. I pay to drain at the Battle Plains, drop EPP Qui-Gon to JP: Audience Chamber, free Han V and retrieve much needed force. On his next turn, he causes all sorts of gross force loss from drains, Rebel Base Occupation and You May Start Your Landing. <br />
<br />
At this point I am sick and tired of him draining me, causing direct damage and me having to pay for all my drains while he can do it for free. So I clear my head and almost start to play smart. I say almost because while I was pinging him for a 1 force lose from my Profit objective as a result of Han being at the JP: Audience Chamber, I had forgotten that Chewie was also at a battleground. Because of this little over sight of mine, I couldve probably caused him to lose another 6 or 7 force. Either way, I eventually get Home One, Bright Hope and broken Artoo up to space and Boushh down to block some drains, but by then the damage was just too much. My one glimmer of hope was the six I was tracking to use with On the Edge for some more force retrieval. The how and the why of it I dont know, but I miss tracked and ended up drawing a 2 or something silly causing me to lose Chewie. But the straw that broke the camels back was Keder the Black being deployed to the Battle Plains after I had lost Sorry About the Mess & Blaster Proficiency from the op of my deck. Uglyjust ugly.<br />
<br />
FL  11<br />
<br />
Highs:<br />
UummmAndy was pretty happy to have finally beaten me<br />
<br />
Lows:<br />
Mis-tracking that 6 and forgetting about Chewie all game.<br />
<br />
<br />
Game 3: My Scum vs. Brads Hidden Base<br />
Well, I have never lost against Hidden Base yet with this Scum deck so I am feeling pretty confident. I start the same as game 1 and he starts Rycar Ryjerd V, Squassin and something else. <br />
<br />
I set up lightning fast at the Audience chamber with Scum and Villainy, Jabba V, Bib, and a couple other aliens. He drops Endor, another system and some guys to Rendezvous Point. I get a drain in at the Audience chamber and set up UruRURURURURuRuRURUURuRURURururUrUrURURrUrURuRUURUrURuRUrU<br />
at the Desert with his bantha, Jabbas Cruiser and some other Aliens. He responds with Kiffex, more guys at the Rendezvous Point and Tanus to the Audience Chamber, causing me to lose about 4 force, followed by an undercover going on the little turd. He moves his mini fleet out to some system and lets me go. I Hutt Smooch Tanus into next week and proceed to drain for 3 force at the Desert and for 2 force at the Audience chamber thanks to Galid. I also deploy Jabbas Cruiser via Power of the Hutt to Kiffex with Xizor and Gela Yeens aboard. On his turn he deploys another system, Boushh and Vanden Willard!?!?!?!? to Tatooine along with an undercover. He spreads out his ships and flips his objective.<br />
<br />
Luckily for me I knew exactly were a Hutt Smooch was in my deck so I use URuRUURuRuRURUrurRUURUr to pull it into my hand. All my drains get canceled even though I have now captured Boushh as well with Hutt Smooch, which he finally grabs. At this point I unleash my secret weaponGardulla! Wait!? Gardulla you say? Yes, indeed Gardulla! Go check her out. Combine her with Lando and you have a wicked force retrieval mechanism. For even better efficiency, try her with Prophetess v! I didnt use her against Kevins MBO because he had too many ones in his reserve deck to risk it but she was coming out to play now! I deploy ZiMH and BiHT to space and start probing everywhere I can. I also spread out on the ground in the hopes of getting a drain in somewhere. He drains me at Kessel and another system. If I remember correctly, he had Kiffex, Bothawui, Kessel, Aquaris, Endor and another system down. At this point, I am spreading out on the ground trying to get drains in wherever I can while flying my three ships around, trying to find his base. I am also retrieving force every turn with Gardulla and Lando, which just makes me wet with excitement. He on the other hand is throwing every spy and kitchen sink in the game at me trying to block those drains that he cant cancel using his objective. He even throws EPP Obi-Wan down with Mercenary armour and an undercover!! I am telling you, this is some wicked stuff here! He is also avoiding my ships in space, going for the drains while retrieving force with Luke and pinging me off with virtual Leebo. More on Leebo later. Of course his hidden base was the last system I probed, Aquaris. <br />
<br />
We only had one big battle which pretty much decimated most of our forces in space. He had Corran Horn, Tycho, Wedge RSL and Ric Olie all aboard a bunch of ships. I initiated the battle and he played Houjix & Out of Nowhere, All Wings Report In & Darklighter Spin and probably something else that I cant remember. This guy had more tricks than Houdini. He drew 3 battle destinies for a total of 10. I had ZiMH, BiHT, some bounty hunter pilots and Boba Fett, BH. I drew 4 destinies, he canceled one with Wedge, and I got a total of 12. He ended up with Luke on R5 with built in R2, someone else onboard anther ship and Leebo on board the Outrider loitering around another system. I lost just about everything except for maybe the ZiMH and I had Jabbas Cruiser with Xizor and Gela aboard at another system. <br />
<br />
From then on it was a cat and mouse game as we moved our ships around trying to get in some drains wherever we could. He had spies at every site so I wasnt doing any damage there. At the end of his turn he had four cards left in his life force while I had 2. Neither of us had any cards in hand. I occupied a battle ground site and system but he only occupied systems, so I knew that if I could just get that drain in at Kiffex for the two, he wouldnt be able to pay to drain and I would win. Remember that Leebo, this is where he comes back to haunt me. During his draw phase, he loses the top card from his reserve deck to make me lose mine. I am now down to 1 card left as it dawns on me what he is about to do. I activate my 1 force and he Leebos me to death. He now has 2 cards left to my none.<br />
<br />
As I write this I realize that he could not have done that because Leebo does it to the top card of your reserve deck, but I had activated my one force. Therefore Leebo could not have done his little trick. That would have allowed me to drain for 2, leaving him with 1 card left and I wouldnt have had any cards left in my reserve deck. The following turn I would have drained him again and won the game by 1. All well, Ill get you next time Brad!<br />
<br />
FL -2<br />
<br />
Highs:<br />
Brad for playing a great game.<br />
I love Gardulla.<br />
Even though I lost, I got a huge kick out of seeing Commander Vanden Willard in a     <br />
deckand Obi-Wan with Merc. Armour and Undercoverclassic! <br />
<br />
Lows: <br />
Getting Leebod to death!! Who gets Leebod to death!!<br />
<br />
<br />
At this point in the day, I had gone 1-2 and I was feeling pretty bad about my record, but I wasnt about to let that deter me.<br />
<br />
<br />
Game 4: My Profit versus Davids Court <br />
In all my play testing, the hardest match up for Profit was always My Kind of Scum so I assumed that going into the match I was in for a hard time. I thought wrong. David started almost the exact same effects as me as well as putting Jabba and Chall Bekan to the Audience Chamber. I start my usual effects hope for the best.<br />
<br />
First turn, he deploys to the Audience Chamber: Lando, Mara Jade, a virtual rodian and 4-Lom via the rodian. He also deploys Jabbas Sale Barge. I on the other hand drop the Naboo: Battle plains with EPP Qui-Gon and Chewie Protector V from hand with naked Threepio to Tatooine. I also lose one force to his objective.<br />
<br />
On his second turn, he deploys Snoova with his vibro-ax to the plains and plays a virtual Twilek advisor, which I promptly sense. Instead he pays for Boba Fett, BH and initiates the battle. In response, I play Impressive, Most Impressive V and cut up Boba with Quiggy. I immediately play SATM & BP to send him to the lost pile. He targets Qui-Gon with the vibro ax and draws higher then me, sending Quiggy to my used pile instead of taking him into custody. This leaves Chewie vs. Snoovathe Rumble in the Nabooian Junglethe Fur vs. the Fang, thewell you get the picture. Snoova has 3 more power then Chewie due to the vibro ax and Jabbas Influence V, so I lose a couple cards to the lost pile and leave Chewie there. <br />
<br />
My turn, I come down hard with EPP Luke and EPP Ob-Wan. I initiate battle and slice up Snoova like there is no tomorrow while he draws low on his ax destiny. Thanks to the Colo Claw Fish, my battle destiny is a six, giving me a total power of 23 to his 9. I dont get too excited cause I figure he has a Ghhhk up his sleeve. Well, I practically yell out in joy when he forfeits Snoova and proceeds to count out a 14 force loss from the overflow. At this point I have won the game, all I have to do is keep up the pressure. I put A Gift on Broken Artoo and deploy Boushh and Honor of the Jedi to stop the force loss to his objective and drains. He eventually puts down No Escape to negate Honor but that just leads me to deploying some guys to Tatooine in order to smack around Mara Jade and her friends. At this point, the game is over and we both know it so we quickly finish up with me coming out on top by a large margin. I think I managed to play Flash v about 5 or 6 times by tracking it around. He must of thought my deck was stacked with them.<br />
<br />
Since the game only takes about 25 minutes to play, David and I sit around comparing decks and strategies. David seems like a really nice guy, someone I would sit around and have a beer with, which makes me feel kinda guilty for beating him so completely. But, cest le vie!<br />
<br />
FW + 29<br />
<br />
Hi: Hitting Snoova for 14 overflow! <br />
<br />
Low: None from my perspective!<br />
