Game 5: My Scum vs. Spencers WYS<br />
Oh my! I know right away that this is gonna be a good game. You see, Spencer is consistently one of the best players at the tournaments I run in Toronto and he is currently the #1 player in Ontario. Far too often it has come down to the two of us competing for first place and the last few times he has beaten me. In fact, we played these two decks against each other at the last Toronto tournament and he won, though I felt that it was a game I could have just as easily won. On top of all that, we are both very competitive and we both like to win, especially against each other!<br />
<br />
So I start my usual and he starts Squassin, Wokling v, and Civil Disorder v. My first turn I get Scum and Villainy, Jabba, Bib and Lando all down to the Audience chamber, giving him lots of force from Drop! V. He starts extremely strong and puts Nightfall on Tatooine via Wokling, Corran for free to the Cantina, Luke aboard R5 with built in R2 to Kessel and pulls the Weapons Display shield. On my second turn, I am activating a billion force thanks to Hutt Bounty. I play Ghhk (which he grabs) to cancel the Nightfall and go after Corran hard. I drop Gardulla, 4-Lom and two other guys. I initiate battle and beat the crap outa Corran until he is bleeding all over Wuhrs bar. I draw some cards, clean up the spilt blood and end my turn. He responds with a drain at Kessel, where I slap Enter the Bureaucrat to fix that problem. He backs up Luke with another ship and matching pilot. Wedge and Red 2 I think. He draws a couple cards into his hand then declares that he is finished. <br />
<br />
Come turn 3, I am activating more force than I will ever need and all my cards deploy for dirt cheap thanks to Hutt Bounty and Scum & Villainy. So my first order of business is to use Gardullas game text and retrieve force, followed by me then dropping some more guys to the Cantina and throw Jabbas Cruiser, ZiMH and some alien pilots on the cruiser and initiate battle. Of course I forgot to occupy a third Tatooine site so my objective isnt flipped yet, meaning that my draws are still normal. Thanks to ZiMH he doesnt get a battle destiny. His Wedge and Red 2 go down in flames while my ships are still nice and sparkling clean.  On his turn he plays friggin Effective Repairs to get back his Nightfall, which gets redeployed, allowing him to drop Tanus for free, causing me to lose a small handful of force while he moves Luke in Red 5 over to Tatooine. <br />
<br />
Naturally, on my fourth turn I send some guys after Tanus, but not before retrieving some more force with Gardulla! But this time I remembered to occupy that third Tatooine site, which means my destiny against Tanus was +3. He responds with EPP Han and Chewbacca v to an unoccupied Tatooine: Jabbas Palace, grabbing Life Debt with Chewie in the process. So after retrieving some more force with Gardulla, I do what this deck does best, battle. I come down with Dengar v (which cancels Hans game text), Greedo (which I use to cancel Chewies game text) and a rodian. I draw some ridiculously high destiny, killing off his two characters and I think I lose Dengar and Greedo to his multiple destinies, canceling one in the process with another Greedo to the objective. <br />
<br />
Now, it may seem like I was just kicking the crap out of Spencer but it was a lot closer than it would seem. I couldnt get out URURUrUrURURUruURURURururur for the big drains and Galid was sitting at the bottom of my lost pile which meant I was only draining for one at Kessel, two at the Cantina and another one at the Audience Chamber. He had Luke retrieving force for him all game and was continuously paying to drain for one at Tatooine. <br />
<br />
He eventually moves Dash and Luke over to Kessel along with some forfeit on his turn in hopes of blocking my drain. I do the Gardulla, Lateral Damage the Outrider and deploy Boba Fett BH to Jabbas Cruiser along with another bounty hunter, initiate battle and practically win the game. He loses everything except Luke on board R5 and I lose some forfeit fodder. At this point he moves Luke over to Tatooine and all but dies. I continue to apply some drains but wait! He deploys Leebo!! Leebo!! I hate friggin Leebo! So he decides to commit seppuku by losing cards from his reserve deck to whittle down the differential. I look on in horror as he manages to take off another 3 or 4 cards from my life force before he dies. It is officialI hate Leebo. Oh and when I get back to Toronto I am seriously thinking about investing in some American Pylon manufacturing companies.<br />
<br />
FW +17 ish<br />
<br />
Hi: Gardulla baby! Gardulla! <br />
      Lateral Damage. Winning games since 1995!<br />
      Canceling Han and Chewies game text with Dengar and Greedo. Classic.<br />
<br />
Low: Nothing. This whole game was one big high!<br />
<br />
<br />
Game 6: My Profit vs. Matts AOBS<br />
Forget Stella! By now I am riding my own groove! Sure I lost two games earlier but I had come back strong so I felt good coming into this match up and I had the utmost confidence in my Big Disco Party that is Profit.<br />
<br />
Surprise, surprise! I start my usual while Matt uses Twilek v which gets him Desilijic Tatoo v, Ket Maliss v, Info Exchange v and Scum & Villainy. He is also the only person who decides to start any aliens at my Audience Chamber all day. He drops EPP Denger and the good Dr. E and his buddy P.B.<br />
<br />
To start, he pulls some guys and the Coruscant: docking bay with Ket Maliss. He also grabs unexpected interruption and something else from reserve. Thanks to him grabbing four cards on his first turn I get to activate three force courtesy of Thrown Back. So anyway, he deploys Bane Malar v to the Cor: docking bay and moves Xizor over to hang out together. <br />
<br />
In my hand I am holding a Qui-Gon, Chewie Protector, and OOC&TT. So I decide to try and end it right there. I activate six force from icons and myself and thanks to those 3 force I got from Thrown Back, I have enough to deploy Threepio from reserve deck to Tatooine for free, Chewie for free to the docking bay, EPP Qui-Gon for 7 force with Chewie and initiate battle. I toss a 6 on the fish to guarantee the hit and slice up Xizor. He draws a 6, causing me to lose 8 from attrition thanks to his objective so I forfeit Chewie first, not wanting to leave him alone. He unfortunately forfeits Bane first then Xizor, with those being the only two cards in his lost pile. After I lose Qui-Gon to satisfy the remaining attrition, I use my last force to play OOC & TT. There is a 50% chance that I will nail Xizor, effectively killing his objective on my first turn. Unfortunately, the Norse gods werent with me this day and I picked Bane. <br />
<br />
After changing into a fresh pair of drawers, Matt deploys No Escape on his second turn to get Xizor back into his hand and just loads up the docking bay with a whole bunch of guys. Now I run into a little problem. I am only activating 6 force and I am only holding 8 cards in my hand, few of which are currently useful. One of those cards happens to be Speak With the Jedi Council, which I would be crazy to play since he could move his entire deck to it the Council with ease and drain for 3 all game. So I Threepio it out of my hand and getthe Jedi Council in exchange. Just great! So I draw a bunch of cards into my hand in the hopes of getting what I need.<br />
<br />
He drains me at the docking bay and causes some direct damage with his objective. He also tosses more guys down to back up Xizor and draws into his hand. Meanwhile I am Threepio-ing like a mad man. I start chucking around used interrupts trying to get my hand size down while digging for useful things. I deploy Boushh to Coruscant to block the drain and draw some more cards. By this point I have all sorts of useful things in my hand but by only activating 6 force, its hard to get an offensive going. On his turn he causes more direct damage and drops some more docking bays. He also draws a couple cards into hand. On my turn I activate more force and deploy Artoo with A Gift to the Audience Chamber. He notices that I have been stockpiling force for the last couple turns and figures that I am about to make a huge assault on him, so he backs up Xizor at the docking bay and Dengar / Dr. E. at the Audience Chamber even more. <br />
<br />
On my turn, I surprise him by completely ignoring him and deploying Savrip, the Naboo: Battle Plains with Corran, Wedge RSL, EPP Obi and Epp Luke there. Those four characters hold the Battle Plains the whole game by themselves and because Luke is at a battleground his objective is flipped to the zero side and it never flips back again. I Alter his Scum & Villainy, grin and end my turn. He has no way of damaging me anywhere so he decided to throw his aliens against me at the Battle Plain. He comes down with 4-Lom, and every other alien in his deck. Whenever he initiates battle I just concentrate on slicing up his character and I refuse to draw battle destiny, causing him to leave at least one or two guys there after he forfeits. Any overflow from power and battle destinies that get past Corran and Wedge is covered by Savrip. On my turn I would initiate battle against whoever he had left at the Battle Plains, slice up someone, draw destiny, cancel his destinies and cause lots of overflow. I would clear the site, get some drains in for a bit until he had regrouped his forces and we would do that all over again. <br />
<br />
At one point he Snipers Artoo with A Gift but I got it back with Flash v, tracked it back into my hand with Threepio and redeployed it on my favourite droid. I also re-tracked Flash back into my hand and started tracking some sixes to use with my Edges. He had also deployed Sando, canceling my Colo. At this point we were one of the only games that was still going. Someone, I think Spencer, mentions to me that I have a good chance at getting in the final confrontation as long as my differential is high enough. So I pretend that I am Gandalf and pull some crafty wizardry out my hat. I draw two sixes for my two Edges and retrieve 10 force. One Edge gets me back the other and Flash gets me back the second. He pulls out the Do They Have a Code Clearance at this point and I decide to try to free Han before I play my Edges and Flash again, which I might point out I had tracked back into my hand. Sometime while all this is going on, the TD walks over and tells us we have 15 minutes left. I figure its not a problem. I deploy Qui-Gon and Chewie down to the Audience Chamber with the intention of freeing Han. It would turn out this was more difficult than it would have seemed. <br />
<br />
I am holding a SATM & BP in my hand I take a look at his characters at the site. He has the Dr. E combo, EPP Dengar and Greedo. I figure if I initiate battle, slice up Dr. E and make him go missing, then he wouldnt be able to draw battle destiny. Dengar only has ability 2 and Greedo has 1. The plan goes off without a hitch except that Xizor v allows your Black Sun agents everywhere to draw battle destiny if unable to otherwise! Stupid Xizor. So I end up losing Chewie and he comes back at me and initiates battle. I figure, no problem, Ill just slice up Dengar and be done with it. Except that Dengar is defense value + 2 because of Desilijic Tatoo and Ket Maliss, so I miss! He draws his battle destiny and I choose not to draw anything because I dont want to lose Qui-Gon to attrition. At this point the TD tells us that there are only 5 minutes left. I realize that if I time out I wont get the two points and I wont be ably to play in the final confrontation. So I look at Matt and say to him, I really dont want to time out. Now, I have to give Matt big props here. He could have slowed right down the last 5 minutes and forced the timed win but instead he showed a lot of class and obliged me by speeding up his game play. So I have just about my whole deck activated except for about 6 cards. I play Flash and initiate a battle against Dengar, taking the top most character into hand from reserve deck. I finally slice up Dengar and he draws battle destiny while I choose not too, resulting in me losing the battle and the character from my hand via Savrip to satisfy attrition. At this point I control the Audience Chamber so I free Han and retrieve 5 force. Thanks to Flash, I also notice that there is a 6 sitting on the top of my reserve deck during my draw phase, so I use one of my Edges and retrieve anther five force and he snags it with Do They Have a Code Clearance. But wait, whats this? Underneath that 6 was a 5! So play my other Edge and retrieve 3 force (-1 because of Code Clearance). I then retrieve another force with Flash and I now have only 2 cards left in my lost pile! I will point out that I was paying for all the force I retrieved this game after the first Edge because he did pull Secret Plans. Just in case you werent keeping track, I retrieved a total of 26 force during this game. 18 from the Edges, 3 from the Flash and another 5 from my objective. I am feeling pretty invincible right now.<br />
<br />
FW + 36<br />
<br />
Hi: The amount of class Matt showed by not being cheap and timing out. Thanks a lot!<br />
      Me retrieving 26 force! Edge is my friend!<br />
<br />
Low: Only activating 6 force at the start. Ouch.<br />
<br />
<br />
So at this point the standings look like this: <br />
<br />
1. James Booker 12 (+97) <br />
2. Brandon Pahl 8 (+91) <br />
3. Brad Eier 8 (+20) <br />
4. Nate Meeker 8 (-10)<br />
5. Adam Hawke 6 (+9) <br />
6. Andrew Hill 6(+18 <br />
7. Matt Sherrington 6 (-22) <br />
8. Kevin Brownell 6 (-29) <br />
9. Matt Pietrangelo 5 (-20) <br />
10. Spencer Ball 4 (-7) <br />
11. David McCure 2 (-127)<br />
<br />
If you were really paying attention you would notice that the sum of my FW/FL reported at the end of each match up is not equal to the supposed +97 that I ended with. This my fault because I never bothered to write them down so I could only guess based on my memory. Sorry if any of them are way off.<br />
<br />
So, I first check with the TD to make sure that a final confrontation is in the plans and he says as long as Booker and I agree to it then its on. So I ask Booker and he says its up to me. I tell him that I drove all the way from Toronto to play in the tournament and I wouldnt mind playing the final matches. Well, Booker could have just said, I clearly beat you in the Swiss portion so I see no reason for a final confrontation. but instead he shows a lot of class and agrees to take me on and for that I appreciate it. So we settle in for the final two games.<br />
<br />
<br />
My Scum vs. Bookers TRM<br />
This being the final confrontation, people are crowding around the table and talking to me. Because of this, I am not paying attention to the game and I pay for that early. I start with my usual and just in case you forgot what that was, Twi&#39;Lek v gets me Power of the Hutt, Ket Maliss v, Jabbas Influence v and Hutt Bounty v to hand. Booker starts the Yavin 4: TR,  Insurrection combo, Colo and Civil Disorder V I think. I may be wrong on that last one.<br />
<br />
So my first turn I deploy the Audience chamber with Jabbas Palace, Jabba v with the Audience Chamber, Scum & Villainy with Jabba, Bib with Power of the Hutt and Lando with Jabbas Influence. He gets to activate a ton of force and take some cards into his hand. During my whole turn I am having multiple conversations with different people, not really paying attention to what I am doing, simply going through the motions. On his turn I continue to have my conversations while he announces that his activating force. My response is yeah, yeah while I continue my conversation. He then declares he is deploying a docking bay fro reserve deck. Yeah, yeah. He then announces that he is deploying EPP Quiggy to Tat: Jabbas Palace. Naturally, being engrossed in conversations with others around the table, I respond Yeah yeah. He then declares that he is Altering Scum & Villainy and that is about the point in time where I realize that I just made the biggest mistake of the tournament. You see, my Scum deck has very little SAC protection, so my first response to him deploying anyone with respectable ability is to always pull the Oppressive Enforcement shield, so that if my opponent does Alter my Scum & Villainy, then it just gets re-cycled. Well, because of all my conversations that were going on, I failed to do this, resulting in Scum & Villainy being the first card that is lost in the game. I feel like I just got kicked in the stomach. Scum & Villainy is such an integral card to the deck. It is the cornerstone to all my force retrieval and now that it is forever gone I can feel the panic starting to well up inside me. So I do the first thing that comes to mind. I start talking smack. I start making fun of cards that are on the table, saying uRuRUrUrUrs name over and over again in funny ways, asking Booker all sorts of questions and just being a plain old pest. Of course Booker doesnt respond to my ramblings but that is ok since I am only trying to throw him off his game. I was really panicking at this point. <br />
<br />
On my turn I pull the Oppressive Enforcement and There is No Try shields for good measure. I Then drop Xizor, Boelo and uruRURuRuRURURRURURururUrururururuuurUrURURUrURuRURUrUuRuRururUrUruRuRururUrURurUUrururUruRuruRUruRurururUruRurrUur to initiate battle. I use Hutt Bounty and Xizor to reduce Quiggys power to zero and he swings at Xizor, drawing a 1 and a 3. He lets out a little congratulatory Yes! but I point out to him that uRuuRUrurrURUruRuRururUrUurURuRurUrURurUrURuRuRuUR makes all his weapon destinies -2 there! He looks at the card to verify then moves on to his battle destiny, but not before I cancel his previously deployed Savrip with my Masterful Move. He draws battle destiny which I promptly cancel with Boelo! You see, boys and girls, URURrurURU is an alien leader, and works well with Boelo. So he loses Qui-Gon and Houjixes away the rest of the overflow. I grab the Houjix and draw into my hand. Perhaps my saving grace was the fact that I drew Ability x 3 into my hand. I am still rambling on with funny sounds and statements that have no bearing whatsoever to the game and cards in play. I wasnt talking every second by any means but I was surprised that he didnt reach over the table and try to strangle me.<br />
<br />
By the end of his second turn, he had a ton of twixs down and Naked Threepio was cycling away at the Throne Room. He comes back at me with EPP Luke (or maybe it was EPP Obi-Wan) and a couple other guys, shooting RURuRurururUrUruRuU and taking out another one of my guys. On my turn, I throw down some more annoying smack along with Ability x 3, Gardulla and some other guys to clear out his characters from Tatooine. I would just like to point out that Hutt Bounty is a beast with your Gangsters. Anyway, this goes on for a couple of turns. He throws down some characters to try and clear a Tatooine site but I keep reducing the power of his characters to zero and canceling his battle destinies with Greedo. I retaliate, retrieving a character into hand with Ability x 3 every time. At some point during all this, I use Gardullas game text and he ends up drawing a one. Even with Lando there is no way I can make it greater than two. So I lose a card from hand, which isnt all that bad because I am holding a lot of ships and there are no systems on the table. Gardulla catches him completely off guard which makes me very happy even though I lost a force. On my next turn I tried Gardulla again but he drew another one. So I lose one of my two Lateral Damages I am holding in my hand. I pay attention to where that one goes and I realize that he is tracking his low destiny to the top. Well, not being a compete idiot (just a partial), I decide to pass on Gardulla for a while. <br />
<br />
So we go at this back and forth battle on Tatooine for quite some time. He never gets a site cleared and I manage to keep a character present every turn. Both of our life forces are getting low. He is starting to look a little concerned but I dont know if it was because my rambling was starting to finally get to him or if it was because he was running out of characters. Either way, he decides to change strategies. I only have about 4 cards in my hand and a Greedo on my objective so he throws Phylo for free to the Coruscant: Docking Bay that he had previously deployed. As soon as I see Phylo hit the table I announce that She will die next turn. I dont know if he believed me or was even remotely taking me serious at this point but either way he backs her up with Corran. Well, of those 4 cards I was holding in my hand, 1 of them was a Boba Fett BH and another was a TwiLek v. So I deploy Boba from hand for 1 force thanks to TwiLek and Greedo for 1 force from the objective. I initiate battle and draw 3 battle destinies, each one is + 2 thanks to my objective which means my total battle destiny was something ridiculously gross. I cant remember what he drew but it didnt matter. I had a 17 power + whatever the three cards where that I drew for destiny compared to his 6 power plus destiny. That pretty much ended the game right there. I also got to successfully use Gardulla one more time before the game ended and that was that.<br />
<br />
FW + 12 ishI cant remember. I forgot to write it down.<br />
<br />
Hi: Losing Scum & Villainy right off the bat but still managing to pull out the win.<br />
<br />
Low: Losing Scum & Villainy right off the bat.<br />
<br />
Final game.<br />
<br />
<br />
My Disco Party vs. Bookers Hunt Down<br />
As soon as I saw this I had to smile. I built my Profit deck with the intent to defeat HD every time. I am so teched out against HD that it shouldnt even be a contest.<br />
<br />
He starts the Imperial Arrest Order combo, Mob. Points combo and his own Colo Claw Fish. At least I think thats what he started. I started Seeking an Audience v, Civil Disorder v and my Sando Aqua Monster to eat his Colo! Victory is mine! I feel good about this match already! <br />
<br />
To be honest, most of this match up is pretty hazy but I will try to recall what I can. I do remember that he invaded Tatooine pretty fast. He got Darth Maul and the Dr. Evazan combo at Tat: Jabbas Palace lightning quick but I threw Boushh down to block the drain. He then threw Sidious with some droid, IG-88 or P-59, to the Audience Chamber. Naturally he couldnt drain there because of my objective so I wasnt worried. He even threw Emperor v down with Maul. During this time I had deployed the Jedi Council Chamber and Threepio. I had been cycling through my hand getting what I needed, letting him stockpile all his guys on Tatooine. Vader did not come down until later in the game but neither one of us lost much force to Visage. In fact, the only time we ever lost any force to it was when I forced the issue, which wasnt very often. He obviously did not want to lose force from it and I wanted to get an Edge in my hand before I started losing to it, so we both kind of forgot about it and played dumb. In fact, about mid I made it a non-issue by killing it with an OOC & TT. <br />
<br />
Once I was ready, I deployed the Naboo: Battle Plains and dropped EPP Luke along with EPP Obi-Wan. Practically ever character in his deck was stuck over on Tatooine at this point so I knew he couldnt hurt me. He eventually tracked a destiny high enough to zap Boushh with the V Emperor but I just simply gifted Artoo and he was stuck draining me for 1. Finally, Lord Vader hits the Battle Plains with Vaders Lightsaber and goes to town against Obi and Luke. He swings and hits one of themcant remember which one (lets just say Obi-Wan) and I miss both my attempts. He then plays I Have You Now and draws 3 battle destinies. I draw my 1 but I dont break his immunity to attrition. I lose the battle, Obi-Wan and a forfeit nine Yoda from my hand thanks to Savrip! My next turn I deploy EPP Qui-Gon and lay the proverbial smack down on Lord Vader. I cut him up good but I dont win the battle so I end up losing Luke, leaving Quiggy to hold the plains on his own, which worries me somewhat. But he ends up leaving Qui-Gon alone for the rest of the game. Also about this time, I pull my retrieve force with a destiny of 6 and On the Edge trick to get back some cards, topped off with a Flash of Insight for good measure. <br />
<br />
On his next turn he deploys Rendili with ZiMH there. I respond with Tantive 4, Bright Hope and Wedge RSL. After I finish up with Zuckuss, it takes me about 2 turns to drain him out. Hunt Down against my Profithe never had a chance.<br />
<br />
FW + uummm.it had to be somewhere around twenty.<br />
<br />
Hi: I dominated this whole game right from the beginning. Oh, and I won the tournament!<br />
<br />
Low:  Hahahahaha!<br />
<br />
<br />
So there you have it! That is how I got to Kalamazoo, Michigan and won myself the chance to design my very own virtual card. Truth be told, now that I have that chance, I have no idea what I am going to do.<br />
<br />
Decks that were played: <br />
<br />
Dark: MKOS, 3 Hunt Down, 2 AOBS, IO (non-v) Yavin, Old School Walkers, Court, Maul deck, SYCFA. <br />
Light: 1 Disco Party, 2 Profit, 2 TRM, Endor Start, WYS, Hyperdrive, QMC, HB, MB<br />
<br />
Now I know your all wondering when this TR report will end but I just wanted to say that since the directions we got from Map Quest had proven to be useless, we had to guess at how to get back to London, so we picked a direction and drove. I am not sure how this happened but we ended up in lost in downtown Detroit. That place has got to be the scariest place ever. I mean it. At 3:00 in the morning, Detroit is absolutely terrifying. We were expecting to get shot at any minute by any number of shady looking people that were prowling the street. Even the cop cars were all beat up and run down. I would also like to point out that Detroit has the worst streets in the world. The road conditions there are awful. I know that the American economy has slowed down over the last couple of years but this is ridiculous. How much could some asphalt cost? <br />
<br />
As far as the whole trip went<br />
<br />
Highs: <br />
Winning the tournament!<br />
Meeting a lot of cool people.<br />
Seeing new places.<br />
BP gas stationslove it.<br />
Gardullaloving her too! She probably retrieved me about 12 force the whole tournament while only giving away 3!<br />
Andy, Spencer and Adam for being great traveling companions.<br />
Michigans motto: Great Lakes, Great Times Classic.<br />
Thanks for running the whole thing Scott!<br />
<br />
<br />
Lows:<br />
Downtown Detroitscary.<br />
Gas for being so expensive.<br />
Turns out that Subway in Michigan serves unsweetened Ice Tea, which tastes just like water with ice cubes!<br />
Having to dodge pylons the whole way there.<br />
What is up with the I-94 being closed?!<br />
Map Quest for proving to be absolutely useless.<br />
<br />
Thanks for the read!<br />
<br />
Later<br />
